description.0: Will Hulk be able to save Betty from the wrath of volcano monsters? The Green Goliath and his lady love are trapped on an island...an island crawling with creatures beyond any conceivable nightmare!
description.1: Are things not what they seem when Iron Man starts attacking New York City? Who will stop the Iron Avenger before he destroys all? Plus: the multi-colored menace called Dr. Spectrum!
description.3: Odin's grave warning of an invasion from beyond threatens all of Asgard. Who, or what, has Thor returning to planet Rigel? The mystery of the Black Stars revealed.
description.4: The newly resurrected Dracula reflects on his life, from his origins as the greatest vampire of all, to his gruesome demise!
description.5: The Fantastic Four and Wyatt Wingfoot find themselves trapped in the lair of Annihilus, where he also has Sue, Agatha and young Franklin as his hostages! Can Reed and his FF teammates save their captive comrades before it's too late?
description.6: Peter encounters a murder scene outside of Mary Jane's apartment. Although M.J. is a first-hand witness, she refuses to call the police out of fear of retaliation. Spider-Man is attacked by his winged enemy Vulture. Could Vulture be behind the murder of a young woman? And if not, who is?
description.7: The final confrontation with Dormammu! The Lord of the Dark Dimension is finally in possession of the Evil Eye, and it will take the combined might of the Avengers and the Defenders to defeat him.
description.8: Who is the Phoenix? You'll gasp when you learn his startling secret identity!
description.12: The start of a sensational new tale featuring a massive menace! World, beware the might of -- IT, THE LIVING COLOSSUS!
description.14: It's a new beginning for Stephen Strange, and new beginnings means healing old wounds! His first stop - making amends with his archnemesis, Baron Mordo!
description.17: Daredevil encounters the mysterious Moondragon! But will they be allies or enemies?
description.18: Peter's aloof behavior draws concern from his classmates at ESU. Plus, Spider-Man encounters a few shadowy figures claiming to be someone they're not. Why is the Kangaroo searching for Spider-Man? And what maniacal plans has he already launched into action?
description.19: The alliance between Dormammu and Loki begins to fray! Swordsman battles Valkyrie in a former Nazi's castle!
description.20: This is it! The final fatal Showdown with the Yellow Claw!
description.21: The dawning of a new era for Captain Marvel! What strange new changes will he undergo?
description.25: Ghost Rider blazes a fiery trail into Spider-Man's path in an effort to stop the entracing Orb!
description.26: The Avengers and Defenders have struck a truce, but no one told Hulk and Thor! Titans clash in a monumental battle of brute strength!
description.27: Will the Harpy triumph over Hulk? If Betty Ross isn't reverted to her former self soon, she may inadvertently kill the man she loves! Plus, attack of the Bi-Beast!
description.28: Iron Man dives head first into a deadly battle with Rokk, the living mountain! All this, and a shocking mystery villain, too!
description.30: Who are these imposters of the gods? Thor returns to Asgard after his battle with the Mercurians to find strange doppelgangers replacing his comrades and family. Just what is going on here?
description.31: Dracula is at last no more....but not for long! One can never truly kill a vampire, especially when he can be revived from the dead!
description.32: Will Reed Richards be able to save his team in the wake of a personal crisis? His marriage may be on the rocks, but Mister Fantastic must take action against Annihilus, ruler of the Negative Zone! Agatha Harkness returns with a grave warning for Franklin Richards.
description.38: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 2: Featuring cameos by Hawkeye, Captain America, Vision, and Klaw!
description.42: Wrath of the Witch-Woman! The malicious mystic has sentenced Johnny Blaze's soul to damnation, and even his powers as Ghost Rider can't help him! Guest-starring Daimon Hellstrom!
description.43: Stephen Strange begins to deal with the fallout from his battle with Shuma-Gorath...and he must say a final farewell to one of his oldest and most trusted friends.
description.47: Kraven the Hunter’s been hired to stalk out and eliminate Daredevil. But who put out the hit? Black Widow may pay the ultimate price for her involvement with Ol’ Hornhead…but not if Matt Murdock can help it!
description.48: Man-Wolf continues to play predator in the streets of NYC. Will Peter discover the true identity of his foe before Man-Wolf strikes again?
description.49: The trickster god Loki has manipulated the Avengers and Defenders into conflict! Will Silver Surfer, Vision, and the Scarlet Witch realize they're on the same side before it's too late?
description.50: Cap, Fury, and the Falcon face off with the seemingly never ending horde of zombies! Who will survive the night of the lurking dead?
description.53: It's underwater mayhew as Spider-Man and Namor must stop the evil plans of Tiger Shark and Dr. Dorcas!
description.55: The misunderstanding between the Avengers ramps up! Now it's Avenger vs. former Avenger as Hawkeye takes on Iron Man!
description.57: The rise of the Harpy! Betty Ross gets a dose of gamma radiation...transforming her into a vengeful monster intent on Hulk's destruction! Will Hulk be able to save Betty from herself, or will the Harpy sink her talons in first?
description.58: Iron Man goes up against light wielding maniac, Dr. Spectrum! If he doesn't defeat this lunatic, it's lights out for everyone!
description.60: Xorr bites off more than he can chew when he attempts to eat a star. On Midgard, Balder's sanity returns!
description.61: The hunt for Dracula reaches a fever pitch! Plus, the origins of Blade are revealed!
description.62: Satana, daughter of the Devil, stars in her first appearance! Also, a witch trial that may go down like the Crucible!
description.63: President Rex Carpenter continues to terrorize Warlock, despite his public approval of the hero. Followers of Warlock meet a tragic end following a demon attack. The concluding issue to Warlock's series, closed with a cliffhanger you have to read to believe!
description.64: The Fantastic Four, trapped in a chasm of death! Wyatt Wingfoot's entire tribe has been swallowed up by Miracle Man's pit- along with Johnny, Medusa and the Thing. Meanwhile at the Baxter Building, a warning from the Negative Zone goes unnoticed by Reed...at his own doom.
description.71: Ka-Zar again refuses to take the Super-Soldier Serum! Will he still be able to defeat Victorius on his own wiles alone?
description.73: The Spirit of Vengenace rides out of hell, and into his very first ongoing series! The Witch-Woman has risen again, and she won't rest until she's got Johnny Blaze in her clutches!
description.74: The final showdown with Shuma-Gorath begins, with the life of the Ancient One in the balance!
description.76: It's a real monster mash-up as the Incredible Hulk takes on the Thing!
description.78: This is it! The long-awaited reunion between Bruce and Betty. Betty's mourning the recent death of her husband, Glenn Talbot. But why is she blaming the Hulk for his demise? M.O.D.O.K. lays the groundwork for his next, sinister plot...all contingent on Betty!
description.79: Tony Stark is ambushed when Whiplash attacks Stark Industries. With Pepper Potts in danger, Tony rockets into action to save her! But can Stark defeat Whiplash before he loses his company and Pepper?
description.81: Sif and Karnilla are privy to Xorr's origin story. Will the Thunder God be able to free his lady love from the God-Jewel...without spelling her demise?
description.84: What sort of trouble has Wyatt Wingfoot gotten himself into? The kind of trouble that requires the FF to make an express trip to Oklahoma! Johnny recounts the FF's first battle with the Miracle Man, as the villain reemerges to terrorize Wyatt's tribe. But to what end?
description.89: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 1: Featuring the first appearance of Erik Killmonger!
description.90: Peter is frustrated by Spider-Man's unfair treatment in the press, particularly in connection to Norman Osborn's death. Plus, Man-Wolf's first appearance! Why is Man-Wolf targeting J. Jonah Jameson? And what are the mysterious forces behind his transformation?
description.91: The Black Knight is missing! The Avengers must travel to Great Britain in search of their teammate. Meanwhile, Dormammu makes Loki an offer he can't refuse!
description.92: After defeating Deadly Nightshade, Queen of the Werewolves, the Star-Spangled Avengers uncovers the identity of Nightshade's hidden leader-The Yellow Cat!
description.93: The Controller has infiltrated Avengers Mansion, and is hunting down the Avengers one by one. Meanwhile, Drax and Thanos clash as the Mad Titan searches for the Cosmic Cube.
description.94: Spidey swings to San Francisco! Set to interview Daredevil and Black Widow for the Bugle, Peter Parker gets a rude intrusion courtesy of Ramrod! What's Ramrod really after? Check out the triple team-up of Spider-Man, DD, and Widow!
description.97: Can Spider-Man and Captain America combined stop Grey Gargoyle from turning the city to stone?
description.98: The Defenders manage to contact the imprisoned Black Knight, who is trapped in another dimension. Loki then deceives the team into collecting the pieces of the Evil Eye!

9.text: Shang-Chi, Master of Kung Fu, in his first ever comic appearance!

11.text: Flea delivers Luke Cage to Comanche and Shades! After the convicts tell Cage how they escaped from prison, the four of them team-up to take down Rackham! Little do they know they are being stalked by a costumed man named Stilletto!

12.text: The start of a sensational new tale featuring a massive menace! World, beware the might of -- IT, THE LIVING COLOSSUS!

13.text: The Werewolf squares off with the Hangman and releases the villain’s captives!

14.text: It's a new beginning for Stephen Strange, and new beginnings means healing old wounds! His first stop - making amends with his archnemesis, Baron Mordo!

16.text: Iron Man is attacked by the Blood Brothers! But the Thing is there to help!

24.text: The mighty Sub-Mariner is broken. Forced to flee by the evil Virago and Orka, Namor has been horribly injured, and is now unable to breathe on land. Only one man has the genius to save him - his greatest rival, REED RICHARDS! Guest-starring the FANTASTIC FOUR!

28.text: Iron Man dives head first into a deadly battle with Rokk, the living mountain! All this, and a shocking mystery villain, too!

34.text: Rackham has taken Mrs. Jenks hostage! To make matters worse, Claire Temple has been accused for the murder of Phil Fox! Luke Cage sets out to learn the truth and speaks with Claire, who assures him of her innocence. Cage vows to find the real killer, and clear Claire’s name!

35.text: After saving a Bavarian gypsy, the Monster becomes witness to the dark witchery of the Black Forest.  Plus, a visitor from Transylvania, and we’re guessing you’ve heard of him - Count Dracula in the undead flesh!

36.text: A horrific car crash beckons Man-Thing out of hiding. What events led to this devastation? Jennifer Kale has an unusual date night with Jaxon. Man-Thing proves an indifferent hero when four victims’ lives are in its hands.

37.text: The Werewolf battles the Hangman at Venice Beach, who thinks he is actually saving Lissa from our hero!

38.text: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 2: Featuring cameos by Hawkeye, Captain America, Vision, and Klaw!

39.text: Carmilla Frost helps Killraven and his Freemen escape the clutches of the horrific Warlord!

42.text: Wrath of the Witch-Woman! The malicious mystic has sentenced Johnny Blaze's soul to damnation, and even his powers as Ghost Rider can't help him! Guest-starring Daimon Hellstrom!

43.text: Stephen Strange begins to deal with the fallout from his battle with Shuma-Gorath...and he must say a final farewell to one of his oldest and most trusted friends.

47.text: Kraven the Hunter’s been hired to stalk out and eliminate Daredevil. But who put out the hit? Black Widow may pay the ultimate price for her involvement with Ol’ Hornhead…but not if Matt Murdock can help it!

52.text: Namor at long last has the upper hand against Virago and her forces, but she suddenly gets an unexpected ally - ORKA, the Human Killer Whale! Can Atlantis survive a combined onslaught?

54.text: Featuring Daimon Hellstrom, the Son of Satan! Ghost Rider is in deadly danger, at the mercy of the Witch-Woman! It's up to Daimon to come to the rescue of his fellow demonic defender!

56.text: Jericho Drumm undergoes his final test for the title of Brother Voodoo!

68.text: Two of Cage’s old cellmates from Seagate Prison break out! At the Gem Theater, Big Ben Donovan pays Cage a violent visit. The two duke it out while Cage’s old cellmates make advancements towards exposing the hero as a felon!

69.text: Despairing and aimless, Frankenstein’s Monster travels to Ingolstadt in the hopes of finding Victor’s family. But what begins as a journey to the past quickly becomes a struggle in the present! The Monster may be part of a feeding frenzy…with a giant spider! An aberration of science meets another abomination.

70.text: Man-Thing has an extraterrestrial encounter when he meets Wundarr, an alien man-child from a faraway planet. Wundarr has been raised without any education or comfort; when he begins terrorizing Citrusville with his superhuman powers, Man-Thing must step in! But does Wundarr understand the havoc he wreaks?

71.text: Ka-Zar again refuses to take the Super-Soldier Serum! Will he still be able to defeat Victorius on his own wiles alone?

72.text: Will Werewolf by Night defeat Sarnak to save his sister and the city of Los Angeles before the Legion of Fear can destroy it?

73.text: The Spirit of Vengenace rides out of hell, and into his very first ongoing series! The Witch-Woman has risen again, and she won't rest until she's got Johnny Blaze in her clutches!

74.text: The final showdown with Shuma-Gorath begins, with the life of the Ancient One in the balance!

76.text: It's a real monster mash-up as the Incredible Hulk takes on the Thing!

77.text: War of the Worlds! Having freed himself from the Martian’s gladiatorial pits, Killraven and his “Freemen” stage an attack on LaGuardia airport!

82.text: Blade and the vampire hunters make a daring attack against the Lord of Vampires!

83.text: When overreaching industrialist F.A. Schist starts tearing up the swamps, the Man-Thing emerges. Featuring Man-Thing’s ‘acidic burn of fear’!

86.text: When a man is mauled to death by abnormally intelligent felines, the mayor of the city hires Luke Cage to investigate the crime! Cage follows a lead and gets attacked by wild cats. With their claws and fangs coated in poison, will the Hero for Hire survive this encounter to solve the mystery? A cat fight unlike any other!

87.text: Our tale continues in Scandinavia! The Monster rescues a young woman from death, discovering he shares more in common with her than any other being. Who is Lenore? Could she be the cure to the Monster’s overwhelming loneliness?

88.text: Jack is kidnapped by Tatterdemalion, a criminal affiliated with The Committee!

89.text: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 1: Featuring the first appearance of Erik Killmonger!

96.text: TRIAL BY COMBAT! Taken captive by the sinister Zephyrean queen Virago, Namor is forced to do battle with the savage sovereign - TO THE DEATH!
